OL,4,CFisherman's Friend tycoon Doreen
OL,5,CLofthouse dies aged 91
OL,6, A pioneering businesswoman who grew
OL,7, Fisherman's Friend cough sweets from a
OL,8, small firm into a huge global brand has
OL,9, died aged 91.
OL,11,FDoreen Lofthouse, known as "the mother
OL,12,Fof Fleetwood", began to spread word of
OL,13,Fthe menthol and eucalyptus lozenges
OL,14,Faround the world in the 1960s.
OL,16,FThe Lancashire philanthropist was
OL,17,Fawarded an OBE for her charity work.
OL,19,FWyre Council said Mrs Lofthouse was "a
OL,20,Ftrue pioneer" whose generosity had also
OL,21,Fhelped "transform Fleetwood".
